.TH "pci_p2pdma_map_sg_attrs" 9 "pci_p2pdma_map_sg_attrs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_p2pdma_map_sg_attrs \- map a PCI peer-to-peer scatterlist for DMA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_p2pdma_map_sg_attrs
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "int nents "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction dir "  ","
.BI "unsigned long attrs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device doing the DMA request
.IP "sg" 12
scatter list to map
.IP "nents" 12
elements in the scatterlist
.IP "dir" 12
DMA direction
.IP "attrs" 12
DMA attributes passed to \fBdma_map_sg\fP (if called)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Scatterlists mapped with this function should be unmapped using
\fBpci_p2pdma_unmap_sg_attrs\fP.

Returns the number of SG entries mapped or 0 on error.
